Bayern Munich beat Porto 5-3 on the night in their Champions League quarter-final second leg at the Allianz Arena . 
  Thiago Alcantara gave the home side the lead after 14 minutes with a header . 
  Jerome Boateng levelled the scores before Robert Lewandowski scored a hat-trick . 
  Thomas Muller and Xabi Alonso completed the scoring for the hosts . 
  Pedro Martinez scored a consolation goal for the Portuguese side . 
 